description.plain:
In Sparke’s Tiny Desk Concert, she had this to say about the song:

I think it was one of the first times that I was in the states and I was in LA, and my friend was like, ‘you really need to drive. You’ve been here for months, you need to get in the car— let’s drive around the block.’ And it was a stick shift, and on the other side of the road, and the truck was huge. And I  just stalled all away around the block, and I was like, I’m done. I’m just gonna stick to playing the guitar and writing music, and I went inside and I think I wrote this song that day, so, the day I drove the car around the block.
